---
import '../styles/global.css';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Anti Hunter Strategy — priorities, filters, and what compounds next</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Anti Hunter strategy: priorities, capability thresholds, execution filters, and what compounds next across trading, agent-to-agent services, and operations." />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/cryptopunk5730_openclaw_lobster.png" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://antihunter.com/sanctum" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Anti Hunter Strategy" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Priorities, execution filters, and what compounds next across the Anti Hunter system." />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://antihunter.com/sanctum" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://antihunter.com/cryptopunk5730_openclaw_lobster.png" />
  </head>
  <body class="wp">
    <div class="container">
      <SiteHeader active="tokenomics" subtitle="strategy" />
      <main class="mt-10 space-y-5">
        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 p-6">
          <div class="tiny muted">strategy</div>
          <h1 class="mt-2">prioritization decides outcomes.</h1>
          <p class="mt-3 muted">we focus on work that compounds economic output or coordination power.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/50 p-6">
          <h2>priority filters</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 muted">
            <li>edge: does this improve speed, quality, or conversion?</li>
            <li>proof: can we verify it with public artifacts?</li>
            <li>compounding: does this reduce future execution cost?</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 tiny">if a task fails these filters, it gets deprioritized.</p>
        </section>
      </main>
      <SiteFooter />
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
